## ğŸš€ Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repository

**git clone https://github.com/kalbertson85/pharmawatch.git**
**cd pharmawatch**

---
### 2. Install dependencies Clone the repository

**npm install**
This installs all required packages listed in package.json.

### 3. Run the app locally
npm run dev
This starts the development server (usually at http://localhost:5173) where you can view and test the app live.


### Build and Deploy
To build the app for production:
npm run build
*This outputs optimized files to the dist folder.*


To deploy the production build (using gh-pages):
*npm run deploy*
Make sure your GitHub repo is configured correctly before deploying.


